snippet: Authorities said a stampede on Tuesday left 16 people dead and 78 injured when a singer atop a Carnival float struck an overhead power line, igniting sparks and panic.
abstract: Stampede at Carnival parade in Haitian capital of Port-au-Prince kills 16 people and injured 78 others, after singer on float hits overhead power line, igniting sparks and panic.

byline.original: By ANDRE PAULTRE and RANDAL C. ARCHIBOLD
byline.contributor: Andre Paultre reported from Port-au-Prince, and Randal C. Archibold from Mexico City.

lead_paragraph: Authorities said a stampede on Tuesday left 16 people dead and 78 injured when a singer atop a Carnival float struck an overhead power line, igniting sparks and panic.

headline.main: 16 Die in Crush at Carnival in Haiti Capital
headline.print_headline: 16 Die in Crush at Carnival in Haiti Capital
